274
00:15:28,900 --> 00:15:30,980
Don't you think she said too much?

275
00:15:30,980 --> 00:15:33,110
I'm just doing my best.

276
00:15:33,320 --> 00:15:35,070
I totally get it.

277
00:15:35,070 --> 00:15:36,110
My momm—

278
00:15:37,900 --> 00:15:40,890
mother also calls me a lot.

279
00:15:40,890 --> 00:15:45,460
And says things like, "You're always working. 
Make sure to take care of yourself."

280
00:15:45,670 --> 00:15:47,960
What a good mother.

281
00:15:47,960 --> 00:15:48,840
Yeah.

282
00:15:48,840 --> 00:15:51,720
I appreciate that she's 
looking out for me, but...

283
00:15:52,850 --> 00:15:55,890
They don't really understand, huh?

284
00:16:07,100 --> 00:16:08,380
You looking at something?

285
00:16:08,380 --> 00:16:09,400
Oh, no.

286
00:16:09,400 --> 00:16:10,110
It's nothing.

287
00:16:13,460 --> 00:16:15,450
I turned around for nothing.

288
00:16:22,680 --> 00:16:25,970
<i>I applied here because I 
was worried about Aocchi.</i>

289
00:16:25,970 --> 00:16:28,460
<i>How did things turn out like this?</i>

290
00:16:43,540 --> 00:16:47,110
You still have ten minutes 
until your lunch break is over.

291
00:16:52,110 --> 00:16:55,110
Ringmaster

292
00:16:52,110 --> 00:16:55,110
In that case, please let Sophia
show you the way.

293
00:17:01,460 --> 00:17:03,470
<i>I can't leave things like this!</i>

294
00:17:03,470 --> 00:17:04,870
<i>I have to make up with her!</i>

295
00:17:20,040 --> 00:17:20,920
Ao...

296
00:17:24,110 --> 00:17:25,750
...cchi...

297
00:17:25,750 --> 00:17:27,190
If you're looking for Aoba-chan,

298
00:17:27,190 --> 00:17:30,450
she went to run an errand for Yagami-san.

299
00:17:30,450 --> 00:17:32,150
I see.

300
00:17:36,600 --> 00:17:39,350
Did Aocchi make all of these?

301
00:17:40,420 --> 00:17:42,040
Oh, yeah.

302
00:17:42,040 --> 00:17:43,520
Like forty or fifty?

303
00:17:43,520 --> 00:17:47,180
You lay them out to make sure 
they all have consistent quality.

304
00:17:48,340 --> 00:17:51,830
But they're all just villagers 
except Sophia-chan.

305
00:17:52,400 --> 00:17:55,050
She joined pretty late,

306
00:17:55,050 --> 00:17:58,550
so all the important characters 
were already done.

307
00:17:58,550 --> 00:18:01,040
But Aoba-chan's doing a really good job,

308
00:18:01,040 --> 00:18:04,800
so I think she'll get to work 
on better characters next time.

309
00:18:06,820 --> 00:18:07,690
Nene-chan?

310
00:18:08,720 --> 00:18:12,190
<i>She's not assigned good 
jobs unless she works hard.</i>

311
00:18:13,030 --> 00:18:15,210
I'm gonna work really hard.

312
00:18:15,210 --> 00:18:18,910
I'm gonna work really hard 
and learn how to do my job.

313
00:18:18,910 --> 00:18:21,900
In order to make a new game.

314
00:18:24,910 --> 00:18:26,500
<i>Aocchi!</i>

315
00:18:48,950 --> 00:18:49,670
Nenecchi!

316
00:18:49,670 --> 00:18:51,060
A-Are you okay?

317
00:19:05,290 --> 00:19:07,020
Th-Thanks.

318
00:19:11,180 --> 00:19:12,270
Um!

319
00:19:12,890 --> 00:19:14,040
Wh-What's up?

320
00:19:15,790 --> 00:19:20,640
You're working so hard with your 
work, but I made fun of you.

321
00:19:21,250 --> 00:19:22,680
I'm sorry.

322
00:19:25,200 --> 00:19:26,350
Oh, no.

323
00:19:26,350 --> 00:19:27,600
I'm sorry, too.

324
00:19:27,600 --> 00:19:31,600
You were just worried about 
me, but I got really mad.

325
00:19:35,860 --> 00:19:39,280
B-But that doesn't mean it's 
okay to overwork yourself.

326
00:19:39,570 --> 00:19:40,980
I know.

327
00:19:40,980 --> 00:19:43,000
I'll watch out for my health.

328
00:19:43,000 --> 00:19:48,040
And I'm really happy that 
you're looking out for me.

329
00:19:50,340 --> 00:19:52,080
Th-Then it's fine.

330
00:19:53,530 --> 00:19:55,680
O-One more thing!

331
00:19:56,940 --> 00:20:03,810
I'm looking forward to 
the finished game, and...

332
00:20:04,550 --> 00:20:06,680
I also support you 100%.

333
00:20:06,680 --> 00:20:09,020
So when your dream to be a 
character designer comes true,

334
00:20:09,020 --> 00:20:10,990
and you release your first game,

335
00:20:10,990 --> 00:20:13,370
you have to give me your first autograph.

336
00:20:13,370 --> 00:20:16,660
I don't know if it'll come 
true, but it's a promise.

337
00:20:16,660 --> 00:20:18,400
It will!

338
00:20:21,610 --> 00:20:24,380
Oh, did you two already make up?

339
00:20:25,830 --> 00:20:26,730
You know.

340
00:20:26,730 --> 00:20:29,080
She finally understood how I felt.

341
00:20:29,400 --> 00:20:31,000
You know.

342
00:20:46,970 --> 00:20:48,270
Sakura-san.

343
00:20:49,160 --> 00:20:49,970
Yes?

344
00:20:49,970 --> 00:20:53,020
I think you should worry 
about yourself first.

345
00:20:53,420 --> 00:20:57,610
I-I-I-I'm sorry!

346
00:22:40,970 --> 00:22:43,530
<i>I hope you'll always be 
the kind person you are.</i>

347
00:23:00,770 --> 00:23:03,170
Ko-chan looked really flustered.

348
00:23:03,170 --> 00:23:04,700
Who's calling her?

349
00:23:05,430 --> 00:23:06,440
It can't be!

350
00:23:11,240 --> 00:23:12,380
I told you!

351
00:23:12,380 --> 00:23:14,200
I work on Saturdays!

352
00:23:15,490 --> 00:23:18,220
Mommy! I'm fine!

353
00:23:18,220 --> 00:23:20,240
I'm not a kid anymore.

354
00:23:20,860 --> 00:23:21,580
What?!

355
00:23:21,580 --> 00:23:23,930
Don't come to my home!

356
00:23:25,630 --> 00:23:28,460
My mom will often come and clean my home.

357
00:23:28,460 --> 00:23:30,650
So that's why your home is always clean.

358
00:23:30,650 --> 00:23:31,840
Are you implying I'm messy?

359
00:23:31,840 --> 00:23:34,450
I'd like to meet your 
mommy, one of these days.

360
00:23:34,450 --> 00:23:36,620
But I don't call her "Mommy," okay?

